  "description": "Practical split-layout contact section: full form on the left (name, email, optional company and topic select, message), structured info column on the right with phone, email, WhatsApp, address, and a tabular hours table. Higher-density counterpart to ContactShapesForm.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Two-column section with the form left and an elevated info aside right. Form fields are labelled with small uppercase mono labels and pair with the SiteGen CtaButton. Info column lists phone / email / WhatsApp / address rows with iconified pills, plus an optional weekly hours table separated by a hairline rule.",
    "usage": "Primary contact section for service businesses with a real address and real hours. Drop in /contact pages, on /about as a closing block, or above the footer on long marketing pages. Use ContactBookingEmbed instead when scheduling is the actual goal.",
    "audienceFit": "Brick-and-mortar service businesses (clinics, agencies, studios), B2B teams that want to publish hours and channels, and any site whose buyers compare 'how do I reach a human' across competitors."
  }
}
